cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with image classification using Saak features, which are obtained through a multi-stage transform similar to convolutional layers in CNNs. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the discriminant power of Saak features, which suggests that it could belong to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions that Saak features are obtained in a one-pass feedforward manner without backpropagation, which could make it relevant to sub-categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
